text: Let me guess: Denzel Washington is going to play: ‚Ä¢ An "Old School", "Street-Smart" African American guy, who follows his own code in life -- A man who... ‚Ä¢ Doesn't like other people telling him-how to live his life.  ‚Ä¢ Abides by the "Old School" approach ‚Ä¢ Calls illegal extra-curricular-activities in his neighborhood -- "The Game". ‚Ä¢ Is keen on teaching his kids about "respect", and how you have to "give it, to get it".  ‚Ä¢ Always makes sure his family is together at the dinner table for "Supper"; Where, they say grace before every meal. ‚Ä¢ Is a Christian who subscribes to the 'word of the lord', but believes that there are certain loopholes when it comes to "providing for his family". ‚Ä¢ Makes sure to tell his children - how bad HE had it - When they get 'outta line'..... ‚Ä¢ Is smart, but cannot truly flourish in life because he has grown stubborn and bitter from traumatic experiences with racism and poverty...  -Does that sound familiar? What a waste. The guy is insanely talented and could be one of the greatest actors ever, but he chooses to play the same character OVER AND OVER, in every film he does. He's like the John Mayer of acting. He's got all the talent in the world; But simply refuses to challenge himself as an artist.

text: Very well told story over grand acting with the best in performing arts;  Davis, Denzel, Mykelti Williamson ( HEAT the infamous Bank Robbing with Val Kikmer, Robert Dinero), Russell Hornsby ( Lincoln Heights). This movie in the highlights of it truths tells the raw sides of real life that could have easily turn tragic given the turn of events if compared to the way people behave and believed during the 50's era verses the ways of most people today.  The reality of marriages that stand the test of time and life as depicted here when Denzel not only had an affair but got the other woman pregnant AND was man enough to tell his wife about it, rather than hide it deny the innocent baby coming into the world. This movie does indeed tell the raw dynamics of the human experience and if you're a person that believes in God you can clearly see the tones of FAITH present throughout this story. Great Job Denzel Washington # Director
